Global Cosmetic Phenoxyethanol Ingredients Market Insights
Cosmetic Phenoxyethanol Ingredients Market size was valued at USD 0.32 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 0.45 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 4.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Cosmetic Phenoxyethanol Ingredients Market Overview
The global cosmetic phenoxyethanol ingredients market size was valued at approximately USD 97.5 million in 2023 and is expected to expand at a CAGR of 5.2% from 2024 to 2031. Phenoxyethanol is a widely used preservative in cosmetic and personal care products due to its antibacterial properties, effective at low concentrations. Increasing demand for skincare, haircare, and cosmetic products is driving the growth of this market. The market is highly competitive, with various players across the globe focusing on enhancing product quality and expanding distribution channels. The market's growth is influenced by the rising consumer preference for preservative-free, natural formulations, which may challenge the industry's growth but open opportunities for innovation. The Asia Pacific region, especially China and India, is experiencing significant demand for these products due to growing consumer interest in personal care.

